$ of a rather flat collapsed mode. We\nanalytically compute the phonon frequency renormalization from high\ntemperatures to the soft mode, and relate it to a peak in the orbital-resolved\nsusceptibility, obtaining an excellent match with both ab initio and\nexperimental results, and explaining the origin of the approximately flat\nphonon dispersion. Our data report the first example of the collapse of a\nsoftening of a flat phonon plane and promote the 166 compounds of the kagome\nfamily as primary candidates to explore correlated flat phonon-topological flat\nelectron physics.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Tue, 18 Apr 2023 17:59:53 GMT"}],"update_date":"2023-04-19"}
