t predict elevated\npopulation-wide SFRs in jellyfish compared to analog satellite galaxies with\nthe same stellar mass or gas fraction. Simulated jellyfish galaxies do undergo\nbursts of elevated star formation along their history but, at least according\nto TNG50, these do not translate into a population-wide enhancement at any\ngiven epoch.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Tue, 18 Apr 2023 18:00:03 GMT"}],"update_date":"2023-04-20"}
