ameters for finite-source microlensing events from\nuniform, and limb-darkened source stars with the average $R^{2}$-scores of\n$0.87$, and $0.84$, respectively. $R^{2}$-score for evaluating the lens impact\nparameter gets worse on adding limb darkening, and for extracting the\nlimb-darkening coefficient itself this score falls as low as $0.67$.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Wed, 19 Apr 2023 09:38:48 GMT"}],"update_date":"2023-04-20"}
